"title": "5102: Moses, life of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5102: moses, life of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The life of Moses sets the scene for the great events of the exodus from Egypt, and the showing forth of the power of the LORD, culminating in the giving of the covenant at Sinai and the preparations for entry into the promised land.</p>\n<h2>The meaning of the name Moses</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod2:10\">EXO 2:10</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Moses' birth and early life</h2>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod2:1-Exod2:3\">EXO 2:1–2:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod2:5-Exod2:6\">EXO 2:5–2:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:20-Acts7:22\">ACT 7:20–7:22</a></p>\n<h2>Moses kills an Egyptian</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod2:11-Exod2:15\">EXO 2:11–2:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:23-Acts7:29\">ACT 7:23–7:29</a></p>\n<h2>The calling of Moses</h2>\n<h3>God reveals himself to Moses at the burning bush</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:1-Exod3:5\">EXO 3:1–3:5</a></p>\n<h3>He is called to deliver his people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:10\">EXO 3:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:7-Exod3:9\">EXO 3:7–3:9</a></p>\n<h3>Moses learns the divine name</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:14\">EXO 3:14</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Moses protests his inadequacy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:11\">EXO 3:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:13\">EXO 3:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod4:1\">EXO 4:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod4:10-Exod4:13\">EXO 4:10–4:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod4:16\">EXO 4:16</a> <em>Moses is given Aaron as spokesman.</em></p>\n<h2>Moses' confrontation with Pharaoh</h2>\n<h3>Moses and Aaron speak to Pharaoh</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod7:6-Exod7:7\">EXO 7:6–7:7</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Pharaoh's disobedience leads to the plagues</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod7:1-Exod7:5\">EXO 7:1–7:5</a></p>\n<h3>The death of the firstborn in Egypt</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod11:4-Exod11:9\">EXO 11:4–11:9</a></p>\n<h3>The institution of the Passover</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:26-Exod12:27\">EXO 12:26–12:27</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Moses leads Israel in the exodus from Egypt</h2>\n<h3>The crossing of the Red Sea</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod14:29\">EXO 14:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod14:26-Exod14:28\">EXO 14:26–14:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh2:10\">JOS 2:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh4:23\">JOS 4:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:29\">HEB 11:29</a></p>\n<h3>Thanksgiving for deliverance from Egypt</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod15:1\">EXO 15:1</a></p>\n<h2>The establishment of the covenant with Moses</h2>\n<h3>Moses is given the Ten Commandments</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod31:18\">EXO 31:18</a></strong></p>\n<h3>He smashes the tablets because of the people's idolatry</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:19\">EXO 32:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:16-Deut9:17\">DEU 9:16–9:17</a></p>\n<h3>He puts the new stone tablets in the ark</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:3-Deut10:5\">DEU 10:3–10:5</a></p>\n<h2>Moses leads Israel in the wilderness</h2>\n<h3>He asks to see the glory of the LORD</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:18\">EXO 33:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:22-Exod33:23\">EXO 33:22–33:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:30-Luke9:32\">LUK 9:30–9:32</a></p>\n<h3>The LORD promises his presence on the journey</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:14\">EXO 33:14</a></p>\n<h3>The construction of the tabernacle</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:32\">EXO 39:32</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb8:5\">HEB 8:5</a></p>\n<h3>Moses inaugurates the Aaronic priesthood</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:30\">LEV 8:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:22-Num6:27\">NUM 6:22–6:27</a></p>\n<h2>Moses on the brink of the promised land</h2>\n<h3>He takes a census before the entry into Canaan</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num1:2\">NUM 1:2</a></p>\n<h3>He sends spies ahead</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num13:1-Num13:3\">NUM 13:1–13:3</a></p>\n<h3>He is vindicated against the grumblers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num16:28-Num16:32\">NUM 16:28–16:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num21:4-Num21:9\">NUM 21:4–21:9</a></p>\n<h3>He is prohibited from entering the promised land</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num20:12\">NUM 20:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut3:23-Deut3:26\">DEU 3:23–3:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut34:4\">DEU 34:4</a></p>\n<h2>Joshua succeeds Moses</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num27:18\">NUM 27:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num27:22\">NUM 27:22</a></p>\n<h2>The death of Moses</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut34:4-Deut34:5\">DEU 34:4–34:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut34:6\">DEU 34:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:9\">JUD 1:9</a></p>",
